flowRoot.flowPara: Site in Tile (SiT): Cube/axial SPoint coords X = (-1,1) in sites relative to tile (-1,0)
Relative to center site of tile
Coord may or may not actually land in the origin tile
Is in tile if coord length <= Integral tile radius
(with or without caches depending on.. rendering?)
Tile in Grid (TiG): Cube/axial SPoint coords X rounds to (-1,0)
Relative to center tile of grid
Site in Grid (SiG): Cube/axial SPoint coords X = (-5,-2) in sites relative to tile (0,0)
Equivalent to Site in Tile of center relative to tile in grid = (0,0)
Tile in Dits (TiD): Cube/axial DPoint coords
